We present a search for the rare flavor-changing neutral-current decay $B^+ 	o K^+ 
u  ar{
u}$ based on data sample of 82 fb$^{-1}$ collected with the BABAR detector at the PEP-II B-factory. Signal events are selected by examining the properties of the system recoiling against either a reconstructed hadronic or semileptonic charged B decay. Using these two independent samples, a combined limit of ${\mathcal B}(B^+ 	o K^+ 
u ar{
u})<5.2 	imes 10^{-5}$ is obtained at the 90% confidence level. In addition, by modifying the particle identification criteria, a limit of ${\mathcal B} (B^+	o\pi^+
u ar{
u})<1.0 	imes 10^{-4}$ is obtained using hadronic $B$ reconstruction. All results are preliminary.
